---
title: Ginger Beef Stir-Fry with Sugar Snap Peas
description: A HelloFresh classic! Tender beef and crisp snap peas are quickly stir-fried with warming ginger and served over fluffy basmati rice. Hoisin sauce adds a touch of sweetness and incredible umami depth.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/ginger-beef-stir-fry-w03-29e87e34.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/ginger-beef-stir-fry-w03-5edee66d.pdf
cuisine: Asian
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 516 kcal
  fat: 12 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1237 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/ginger-beef-stir-fry-5841c1fd6121bb50614be8e2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{2 2/3%cups} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Trim @sugar snap peas{12%ounce}. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Thinly slice @scallions{4}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}.

Once water is boiling, add @basmati rice{1 1/2%cups} to #pot{}, cover, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered.

Meanwhile, whisk together garlic, ginger, @soy sauce{2%ounce}, 2 TBSP water, and @hoisin sauce{4%TBSP} in a #small bowl{}.

> We sent more hoisin sauce - use 4 TBSP only.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @beef sirloin tips{16%ounce} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add to pan and toss until nearly cooked to desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove and set aside.

Add snap peas and scallions to same pan over medium heat. (TIP: If veggies seem dry, add a drizzle of oil.) Cook until tender but still crisp, ~{3-4%minutes}, tossing occasionally. Add steak and sauce to pan and cook until sauce is thickened and meat reaches desired doneness, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide between plates, then top with stir-fry and garnish with @sesame seeds{2%TBSP}.